<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1373,1922]" box="[197,1120,1485,1511]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,1485,1511]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks:</emphasis>
A detailed description of this species is given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. &amp; Strack, H. L." box="[903,1117,1485,1511]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref22247" refString="Kaas, P., Van Belle, R. A. &amp; Strack, H. L. (2006) Monograph of Living Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora). Volume 6. Suborder Ischnochitonina (concluded): Schizochitonidae; Chitonidae. Additions to Volumes 1 - 5. Brill, Leiden- Boston, 463 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Kaas 
<emphasis box="[969,1020,1485,1510]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1373,1922]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
We attribute this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guilding" authorityYear="1829" box="[644,818,1523,1548]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Acanthopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[644,818,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Acanthopleura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
following 
<bibRefCitation author="Brooker, L. R." box="[949,1135,1522,1548]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref20975" refString="Brooker, L. R. (2003) Revision of Acanthopleura Guilding, 1829 (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) based on light and electron microscopy. Murdoch University, Western Australia, Thesis, xiii + 528 pp." type="book" year="2003">Brooker (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. This author, on the basis of a cladistic analysis based on a high number of characters (222), concludes that the position of the three species that formerly belonged to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nierstrasz" authorityYear="1905" box="[668,839,1597,1622]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Squamopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[668,839,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Squamopleura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith, 1884)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[856,1330,1597,1623]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Acanthopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="curtisiana">
<emphasis box="[856,1156,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Acanthopleura curtisiana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, E. A." box="[1172,1320,1597,1623]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="487 - 508" refId="ref23571" refString="Smith, E. A. (1884) Mollusca. Pt. 1. The collections from Melanesia. In: Report on the Zoological Collections made in the Indo-Pacific Ocean during the voyage of H. M. S. &quot; Alert &quot; 1881 - 82. Trustees of the British Museum, London, pp. 34 - 116, 487 - 508, pls 4 - 7." type="journal article" year="1884">Smith, 1884</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Carpenter in Pilsbry" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[1341,1436,1597,1622]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Squamopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="miles">
<emphasis box="[1341,1436,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. miles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Carpenter in Pilsbry, 1893), and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hedley, 1898)" baseAuthorityName="Hedley" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[548,917,1634,1660]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Acanthopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="araucariana">
<emphasis box="[548,728,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. araucariana</emphasis>
(Hedley, 1898)
</taxonomicName>
] has a terminal clade within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guilding" authorityYear="1829" box="[1261,1436,1635,1660]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Acanthopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1261,1436,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Acanthopleura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and this justifies 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, A. J." box="[352,550,1672,1698]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="448 - 452" refId="ref21422" refString="Ferreira, A. J. (1986) A revision of the genus Acanthopleura Guilding, 1829. The Veliger, 28, 448 - 452." type="journal article" year="1986">Ferreira’s (1986)</bibRefCitation>
synonymy of this genus with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guilding" authorityYear="1829" box="[908,1082,1672,1697]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Acanthopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[908,1082,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Acanthopleura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This synonymy has not been without controversy, and mainly relates to the various definitions of scales as opposed to spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1373,1922]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, E. A." box="[197,352,1746,1772]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="589 - 630" refId="ref23643" refString="Smith, E. A. (1903) Marine Mollusca. In: Gardiner, J. S., The Fauna and Geography of the Maldive and Laccadive Archipelagoes. Cambridge, University Press, 589 - 630, pls 35 - 36." type="book chapter" year="1903">Smith (1903)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[661,770,1746,1772]" name="Maldives" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Maldives</collectingCountry>
but we failed to find this species, and give an illustration of a specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[385,456,1784,1810]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1373,1922]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,362,1821,1847]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distribution:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Carpenter in Pilsbry" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[371,619,1821,1846]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Acanthopleura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="miles">
<emphasis box="[371,619,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Acanthopleura miles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very common intertidal species, widely distributed in the Indo- Pacific, from the 
<collectingCountry box="[356,544,1858,1884]" name="Maldives" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Maldive Islands</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[603,718,1858,1884]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
in the west to New 
<collectingCountry box="[956,1041,1858,1884]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Guinea</collectingCountry>
in the east, and from 
<collectingCountry box="[1299,1388,1858,1884]" name="Taiwan" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry box="[151,286,1896,1922]" name="Philippines" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[347,414,1896,1922]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Japan</collectingCountry>
in the north to northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[754,861,1896,1922]" name="Australia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Australia</collectingCountry>
in the south.
</paragraph>
